{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019DyDhoiLUHjcDFJ9RMvV54","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me write the harness.\n\nThe harness will:\n1. Write fuzz data to temp file\n2. Open as HDF5 file (read-only)\n3. Use H5Ovisit3 to traverse all objects\n4. For named datatypes, open with H5Topen2 using the object name\n5. Recursively introspect the type class\n\nWait, one issue: In the H5Ovisit3 callback, the `obj` parameter is the root object (the file handle in our case), and `name` is the relative path. \n\nInside the callback, I can use H5Topen2 with the file_id and the name path to access the datatype directly, or I might be able to use the obj parameter itself if it's already the opened datatype object. I'll pass the file ID through the callback's op_data parameter, then use H5Topen2 with the file ID and object name to properly open named datatypes when encountered. Now I'm ready to write the visitor harness.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":905,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1613,"cache_read_input_tokens":36931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1613,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e09d83d7-89d6-46e2-ab74-f025b74c6fac","uuid":"592f1152-6f1c-441e-85eb-bd075335aa04"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019DyDhoiLUHjcDFJ9RMvV54","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context. Let me write the harness:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":905,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1613,"cache_read_input_tokens":36931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1613,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e09d83d7-89d6-46e2-ab74-f025b74c6fac","uuid":"c3a84188-a84b-4ab2-b4af-47ed660b12d7"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019DyDhoiLUHjcDFJ9RMvV54","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Hxh9SS3baXF5tvkNyJhT2S","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/work/harness-proj/fuzz-proj/h5_committed_type_fuzzer.c","content":"/* Copyright 2024 Google LLC\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\n/*\n * Fuzzing harness for committed (named) datatype open and introspection.\n *\n * Exercises: H5Topen2, H5Tget_class, H5Tget_size, H5Tget_nmembers,\n *            H5Tget_member_type, H5Tget_member_offset, H5Tis_variable_str,\n *            H5Tclose  — and supporting helpers like H5Tget_super,\n *            H5Tget_array_ndims/dims2, H5Tget_member_name.\n *\n * Attack surface: The committed-type descriptor is stored verbatim in the\n * HDF5 file and decoded on H5Topen2.  Compound, enum, vlen, and array type\n * descriptors are deeply nested and hand-parsed; historically a rich source\n * of OOB/UAF bugs.\n */\n\n#include \"hdf5.h\"\n\n#include <stdint.h>\n#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\n#include <string.h>\n#include <unistd.h>\n\n/* Maximum recursion depth when introspecting nested types */\n#define MAX_DEPTH 8\n\n/* Forward declaration */\nstatic void introspect_type(hid_t type_id, int depth);\n\n/* Recursively introspect a datatype, honouring API preconditions. */\nstatic void introspect_type(hid_t type_id, int depth)\n{\n    if (depth >= MAX_DEPTH)\n        return;\n    if (type_id < 0)\n        return;\n\n    /* Always valid for any type */\n    H5T_class_t cls  = H5Tget_class(type_id);\n    size_t       sz  = H5Tget_size(type_id);\n    (void)sz;\n\n    switch (cls) {\n\n    case H5T_COMPOUND: {\n        int nmembers = H5Tget_nmembers(type_id);\n        if (nmembers < 0)\n            break;\n        for (int i = 0; i < nmembers; i++) {\n            /* H5Tget_member_name returns malloc'd string; caller must free. */\n            char *mname = H5Tget_member_name(type_id, (unsigned)i);\n            if (mname)\n                H5free_memory(mname);\n\n            size_t off = H5Tget_member_offset(type_id, (unsigned)i);\n            (void)off;\n\n            /* H5Tget_member_type returns a new type ID that must be closed. */\n            hid_t mtype = H5Tget_member_type(type_id, (unsigned)i);\n            if (mtype >= 0) {\n                introspect_type(mtype, depth + 1);\n                H5Tclose(mtype);\n            }\n        }\n        break;\n    }\n\n    case H5T_ENUM: {\n        /* Enum: valid to call H5Tget_nmembers; member values via\n         * H5Tget_member_value; base type via H5Tget_super. */\n        int nmembers = H5Tget_nmembers(type_id);\n        if (nmembers < 0)\n            break;\n        for (int i = 0; i < nmembers; i++) {\n            char *mname = H5Tget_member_name(type_id, (unsigned)i);\n            if (mname)\n                H5free_memory(mname);\n\n            /* H5Tget_member_value writes into caller-supplied buffer;\n             * we pass a suitably-sized buffer for the base type. */\n            long long val = 0;\n            H5Tget_member_value(type_id, (unsigned)i, &val);\n        }\n        /* Introspect the integer base type */\n        hid_t super = H5Tget_super(type_id);\n        if (super >= 0) {\n            introspect_type(super, depth + 1);\n            H5Tclose(super);\n        }\n        break;\n    }\n\n    case H5T_VLEN: {\n        /* Variable-length sequence or string */\n        htri_t is_vstr = H5Tis_variable_str(type_id);\n        (void)is_vstr;\n\n        hid_t super = H5Tget_super(type_id);\n        if (super >= 0) {\n            introspect_type(super, depth + 1);\n            H5Tclose(super);\n        }\n        break;\n    }\n\n    case H5T_ARRAY: {\n        /* Array type: ndims, dims, element type */\n        int ndims = H5Tget_array_ndims(type_id);\n        if (ndims > 0 && ndims <= 32) {\n            hsize_t dims[32];\n            H5Tget_array_dims2(type_id, dims);\n        }\n        hid_t super = H5Tget_super(type_id);\n        if (super >= 0) {\n            introspect_type(super, depth + 1);\n            H5Tclose(super);\n        }\n        break;\n    }\n\n    case H5T_STRING: {\n        /* Fixed- or variable-length string */\n        htri_t is_vstr = H5Tis_variable_str(type_id);\n        (void)is_vstr;\n        break;\n    }\n\n    default:\n        /* INTEGER, FLOAT, BITFIELD, OPAQUE, REFERENCE, TIME — leaf types,\n         * no further nested APIs to call beyond get_class/get_size. */\n        break;\n    }\n}\n\n/* --------------------------------------------------------------------- */\n\n/* op_data passed into the H5Ovisit3 callback */\ntypedef struct {\n    hid_t file_id;\n} visit_data_t;\n\n/* H5Ovisit3 callback: called for every object in the file hierarchy. */\nstatic herr_t visit_cb(hid_t obj_id, const char *name,\n                        const H5O_info2_t *info, void *op_data)\n{\n    (void)obj_id; /* use file_id in op_data for reproducible open */\n\n    if (info->type != H5O_TYPE_NAMED_DATATYPE)\n        return 0; /* only care about committed (named) types */\n\n    visit_data_t *vd = (visit_data_t *)op_data;\n\n    /* Open the committed type the same way a real application would. */\n    hid_t type_id = H5Topen2(vd->file_id, name, H5P_DEFAULT);\n    if (type_id < 0)\n        return 0;\n\n    introspect_type(type_id, 0);\n\n    H5Tclose(type_id);\n    return 0; /* continue iteration */\n}\n\n/* --------------------------------------------------------------------- */\n\nint LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput(const uint8_t *data, size_t size)\n{\n    /* Suppress HDF5 error messages to keep output clean */\n    H5Eset_auto2(H5E_DEFAULT, NULL, NULL);\n\n    char filename[64];\n    snprintf(filename, sizeof(filename), \"/tmp/h5ct_%d\", getpid());\n\n    /* Write fuzz input to a temp file */\n    FILE *fp = fopen(filename, \"wb\");\n    if (!fp)\n        return 0;\n    if (size > 0)\n        fwrite(data, 1, size, fp);\n    fclose(fp);\n\n    /* Open the file read-only — a named-type reader never writes. */\n    hid_t file_id = H5Fopen(filename, H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);\n    if (file_id < 0) {\n        unlink(filename);\n        return 0;\n    }\n\n    /* Traverse every object and exercise the type introspection APIs on\n     * any committed (named) datatype we find. */\n    visit_data_t vd;\n    vd.file_id = file_id;\n    H5Ovisit3(file_id, H5_INDEX_NAME, H5_ITER_NATIVE, visit_cb, &vd,\n               H5O_INFO_BASIC);\n\n    H5Fclose(file_id);\n    unlink(filename);\n    return 0;\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":905,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1613,"cache_read_input_tokens":36931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1613,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e09d83d7-89d6-46e2-ab74-f025b74c6fac","uuid":"18187b94-2592-43c4-8144-3cedf52c9d64"}
