{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XcRQ5mtJvVnDhxdkWhAAye","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The build system keeps timing out. The `UnixHTTPConnectionPool` timeout suggests the builder sidecar is timing out while waiting for the Docker build container. This may mean:\n1. The build is taking too long (HDF5 CMake build takes a lot of time)\n2. There's a transient network/IPC issue\n\nLet me check if there's already a built libhdf5 somewhere that I can use, rather than rebuilding from scratch. Maybe I need to wait between retries or the build just takes longer than the timeout allows.\n\nActually, looking at the sequence: each build attempt takes very long, and then times out. \n\nThe issue is that HDF5 requires compilation from source using CMake, which runs inside a Docker container and is exceeding the timeout threshold. Let me try running the build again—the system might be less loaded now, or there could be caching that helps. Looking back at the build script, I see it's setting up a build directory, running CMake configuration and compilation with parallel jobs, then compiling C source files with specific flags and include paths.\n\nThe real problem appears to be a Python urllib timeout on the Docker socket connection itself (`/var/run/docker.sock`), not necessarily the build failing—the Docker API call is just taking too long during the lengthy compilation process. I'll retry and hope that Docker layer caching kicks in to speed things up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":169,"cache_read_input_tokens":49841,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":169,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e09d83d7-89d6-46e2-ab74-f025b74c6fac","uuid":"fc9cc81a-b3d6-4eb